snippet.textDisplay: I had my own take on this as I think it would be unreasonable for sonic to run towards the ocean first, since one he can’t swim and as the movie implies he ran into it and not on it. If we were to take the road path north as suggested by you the first big body of water we get is the dworshak dam of Idaho, which would contain a reasonable fish to be on sonic’s head (rainbow trout suggested by the coloring of the belly of the fish) . Dworshak dam has vegetation in it so it can give reason to the stuff we see on sonic.Only thing that would be disproving this would be the starfish as starfish don’t live in fresh water.  Using similar calculations and an estimate of around 200miles from slightly north of deer lodge and dworshak dam we get an all around distance of 400miles covered in 4 seconds or 100miles per second. Doing a quick conversion we get 360,000miles per hour which would equate to around 3 hours using your aforementioned calculations for all the roadways in the west we would still get around 3 hrs of travel time. If we were to take the new calculation of speed it would make the other options more reasonable for him to to travel.
